Agent goals: structured short/medium/long horizons persist across turns

Agents now declare three goal horizons on every turn via the LLM JSON
schema. The goals are persisted on the Player model and surfaced at the
TOP of the next turn's action_hint, creating a commitment mechanism so
plans like "save 45k then buy cargotran" actually get executed rather
than drifting into endless organics grinding (v7/v8 sanity regression).

- Player gains goal_short/goal_medium/goal_long (<=240c each).
- Observation mirrors goals into obs.goals + a YOUR GOALS hint line.
- Empty-goals state nudges the agent to declare them.
- Action carries optional goal updates; None=keep, ""=clear, str=replace.
- LLMAgent parser accepts both nested {goals:{...}} and flat goal_short=...
- SYSTEM_PROMPT teaches the schema + GOAL DISCIPLINE section + updated
  Day-1 worked example showing goals set and refined across turns.
- Prompt now advises upgrading at CargoTran (43k) instead of 100k.
- 8 new regression tests cover parser shapes, observation surfacing,
  empty-state nudge, runner persistence semantics, and prompt teaching.
- All 114 tests pass, ruff clean.
